<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="232" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,789,2038]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,789,814]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The male adult of this species can be separated from all the other congeners by the combination of the following characters: (
<number box="[404,416,826,850]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" value="1.0">1</number>
) costal membrane basal to bulla without cross veins (
<figureCitation box="[1014,1083,825,850]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[286,1309,193,1928]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[286,1309,193,1930]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 9. Wings of male imagos. 2, Thraulodes luizgonzagai sp. nov., forewing; 3, idem, hind wing; 4, T. sternimaculatus sp. nov., forewing; 5, idem, hind wing; 6, T. alapictus sp. nov., forewing; 7, idem, hind wing; 8, T. pinhoi sp, nov., forewing; 9, idem, hind wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222477/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">
Fig. 
<number box="[1066,1083,826,850]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
); (
<number box="[1112,1127,826,850]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" value="2.0">2</number>
) costal and subcostal zones of forewing translucent (
<figureCitation box="[449,524,861,886]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[286,1309,193,1928]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[286,1309,193,1930]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 9. Wings of male imagos. 2, Thraulodes luizgonzagai sp. nov., forewing; 3, idem, hind wing; 4, T. sternimaculatus sp. nov., forewing; 5, idem, hind wing; 6, T. alapictus sp. nov., forewing; 7, idem, hind wing; 8, T. pinhoi sp, nov., forewing; 9, idem, hind wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222477/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">
Fig. 
<number box="[508,524,862,886]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
); (
<number box="[562,576,862,886]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" value="3.0">3</number>
) two dark brown bands on femora (
<figureCitation box="[1028,1120,861,886]" captionStart="FIGURES 18 – 22" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1791,1814]" captionTargetBox="[166,1436,193,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[166,1451,193,1744]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 18 – 22. Thraulodes luizgonzagai sp. nov.: 18, lateral view (freshly killed specimen); 19, lateral view (fixed specimen); 20, dorsal view (fixed specimen); 21, detail of prosternum; 22, detail of foreleg (scales: 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222479/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">
Fig. 
<number box="[1088,1120,862,886]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
); (
<number box="[1155,1170,862,886]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" value="4.0">4</number>
) terga in dorsal view predominantly light brown, in lateral view translucent whitish, with three distinct spots on terga II–VI and one spot on terga VII–VIII (
<figureCitation box="[372,510,933,958]" captionStart="FIGURES 18 – 22" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1791,1814]" captionTargetBox="[166,1436,193,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[166,1451,193,1744]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 18 – 22. Thraulodes luizgonzagai sp. nov.: 18, lateral view (freshly killed specimen); 19, lateral view (fixed specimen); 20, dorsal view (fixed specimen); 21, detail of prosternum; 22, detail of foreleg (scales: 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222479/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">
Figs. 
<number box="[437,510,934,958]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" value="19.5" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="19.0">19–20</number>
</figureCitation>
; (
<number box="[533,547,933,958]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" value="5.0">5</number>
) subapical spines of penes long and narrow, apicolateral area not forming an “ear”, lateral pouch present, and without recurved folds (
<figureCitation box="[787,912,969,994]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 17" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1863,1886]" captionTargetBox="[195,1406,193,1776]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[170,1412,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 17. Genitalia of male imagos. 10, Thraulodes luizgonzagai sp. nov., genitalia (ventral view); 11, idem, penes (ventral view); 12, T. sternimaculatus sp. nov., genitalia (ventral view); 13, idem, penes (ventral view); 14, T. alapictus sp. nov., genitalia (ventral view); 15, idem, penes (ventral view); 16, T. pinhoi sp, nov. genitalia (ventral view); 17, idem, penes (ventral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222478/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">
Fig. 
<number box="[840,912,970,994]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" value="10.5" valueMax="11.0" valueMin="10.0">10–11</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="232" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,789,2038]" box="[199,1346,1005,1030]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,347,1005,1030]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Male imago.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[354,432,1005,1030]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Length</emphasis>
: body, 
<quantity box="[514,603,1005,1030]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.5 mm</quantity>
; forewing, 
<quantity box="[730,819,1005,1030]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.8" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" unit="mm" value="5.8">5.8 mm</quantity>
; hind wing, 
<quantity box="[957,1046,1006,1030]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" unit="mm" value="1.1">1.1 mm</quantity>
; general coloration brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,789,2038]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">
<emphasis box="[199,260,1041,1066]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[276,415,1041,1066]" captionStart="FIGURES 18 – 22" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1791,1814]" captionTargetBox="[166,1436,193,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[166,1451,193,1744]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 18 – 22. Thraulodes luizgonzagai sp. nov.: 18, lateral view (freshly killed specimen); 19, lateral view (fixed specimen); 20, dorsal view (fixed specimen); 21, detail of prosternum; 22, detail of foreleg (scales: 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222479/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">
Figs. 
<number box="[340,415,1042,1066]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" value="18.5" valueMax="19.0" valueMin="18.0">18–19</number>
</figureCitation>
): dark brown; antenna yellowish brown with scape lighter; upper portion of eye yellowish brown, lower portion black; ocelli white with a black ring at base.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,789,2038]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">
<emphasis box="[199,280,1113,1138]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[303,448,1113,1138]" captionStart="FIGURES 18 – 22" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1791,1814]" captionTargetBox="[166,1436,193,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[166,1451,193,1744]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 18 – 22. Thraulodes luizgonzagai sp. nov.: 18, lateral view (freshly killed specimen); 19, lateral view (fixed specimen); 20, dorsal view (fixed specimen); 21, detail of prosternum; 22, detail of foreleg (scales: 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222479/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">
Figs. 
<number box="[373,448,1114,1138]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" value="20.0" valueMax="21.0" valueMin="19.0">19–21</number>
</figureCitation>
): general color of pro-, meso and metanotum chestnut, with sutures dark brown. Mesonotum with whitish cup-shaped spot on mesoscutelum, posterior region with scuto scutelar suture whitish. Pleura whitish washed with red. Pro- and mesosternum whitish; furcasternum dark brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,789,2038]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">
<emphasis box="[199,266,1222,1245]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Wings</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[291,408,1221,1246]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[286,1309,193,1928]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[286,1309,193,1930]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 9. Wings of male imagos. 2, Thraulodes luizgonzagai sp. nov., forewing; 3, idem, hind wing; 4, T. sternimaculatus sp. nov., forewing; 5, idem, hind wing; 6, T. alapictus sp. nov., forewing; 7, idem, hind wing; 8, T. pinhoi sp, nov., forewing; 9, idem, hind wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222477/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">
Figs. 
<number box="[362,408,1222,1246]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3</number>
</figureCitation>
): forewing membrane hyaline, with dark spot near base; costal and subcostal zones translucent; veins ICu 
<number box="[397,410,1258,1282]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" value="2.0">2</number>
and CuP not joined basally. Costal membrane basal to bulla without cross veins and 
<number box="[1358,1372,1258,1282]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" value="8.0">8</number>
cross veins distal to bulla. 
<collectingCountry box="[383,439,1293,1318]" name="India" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Hind</collectingCountry>
wing hyaline, with dark spot near base and 
<number box="[932,946,1294,1318]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" value="4.0">4</number>
cross veins.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,789,2038]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">
<emphasis box="[199,252,1330,1353]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Legs</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[266,350,1329,1354]" captionStart="FIGURES 18 – 22" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1791,1814]" captionTargetBox="[166,1436,193,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[166,1451,193,1744]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 18 – 22. Thraulodes luizgonzagai sp. nov.: 18, lateral view (freshly killed specimen); 19, lateral view (fixed specimen); 20, dorsal view (fixed specimen); 21, detail of prosternum; 22, detail of foreleg (scales: 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222479/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">
Fig. 
<number box="[318,350,1330,1354]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
): femur with two dark brown bands; apical 
<number box="[834,844,1330,1354]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[855,869,1330,1354]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" value="3.0">3</number>
of femur tinged with light brown and inner margin washed with black. Tibiae and tarsi light brown. Tarsi pale yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,789,2038]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">
<emphasis box="[199,305,1401,1426]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[320,459,1401,1426]" captionStart="FIGURES 18 – 22" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1791,1814]" captionTargetBox="[166,1436,193,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[166,1451,193,1744]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 18 – 22. Thraulodes luizgonzagai sp. nov.: 18, lateral view (freshly killed specimen); 19, lateral view (fixed specimen); 20, dorsal view (fixed specimen); 21, detail of prosternum; 22, detail of foreleg (scales: 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222479/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">
Figs. 
<number box="[384,459,1402,1426]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" value="19.0" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="18.0">18–20</number>
</figureCitation>
): terga predominantly light brown. In lateral view translucent brown, with two isolated spots and two stigmatic dots on terga III–VI, and one isolated spot and a blackish stripe on terga VII–IX. In dorsal view, terga segments I, VII–IX brown and II–VI translucent with posterior margin light brown. Terga segments I– III and VI–VII medially with blackish dorsal mark. Sterna I–VI translucent and VII–X brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,789,2038]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">
<emphasis box="[199,305,1545,1570]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[323,463,1545,1570]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 17" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1863,1886]" captionTargetBox="[195,1406,193,1776]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[170,1412,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 17. Genitalia of male imagos. 10, Thraulodes luizgonzagai sp. nov., genitalia (ventral view); 11, idem, penes (ventral view); 12, T. sternimaculatus sp. nov., genitalia (ventral view); 13, idem, penes (ventral view); 14, T. alapictus sp. nov., genitalia (ventral view); 15, idem, penes (ventral view); 16, T. pinhoi sp, nov. genitalia (ventral view); 17, idem, penes (ventral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222478/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">
Figs. 
<number box="[389,463,1546,1570]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" value="10.5" valueMax="11.0" valueMin="10.0">10–11</number>
</figureCitation>
): forceps pale yellow, segment II washed with black. Posterior margin of subgenital plate almost straight, with a medial rounded projection. Penes pale yellow; 
<number box="[1018,1032,1582,1606]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number box="[1042,1054,1582,1606]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" value="3.0">3</number>
of penes divided apically, with a pair of long and narrow subapical spines, 2.0x the width of penes; apicolateral area not forming an “ear”; external margin forming lateral pouch and without recurved folds parallel to inner margin. Terminal filament whitish, basal area of segments black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,789,2038]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">
<emphasis box="[199,314,1726,1749]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Variations</emphasis>
: Some specimens show color patterns overall darker (
<figureCitation box="[940,1023,1725,1750]" captionStart="FIGURES 18 – 22" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1791,1814]" captionTargetBox="[166,1436,193,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[166,1451,193,1744]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 18 – 22. Thraulodes luizgonzagai sp. nov.: 18, lateral view (freshly killed specimen); 19, lateral view (fixed specimen); 20, dorsal view (fixed specimen); 21, detail of prosternum; 22, detail of foreleg (scales: 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222479/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">
Fig. 
<number box="[994,1023,1726,1750]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
) or lighter (
<figureCitation box="[1164,1248,1725,1750]" captionStart="FIGURES 18 – 22" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1791,1814]" captionTargetBox="[166,1436,193,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[166,1451,193,1744]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 18 – 22. Thraulodes luizgonzagai sp. nov.: 18, lateral view (freshly killed specimen); 19, lateral view (fixed specimen); 20, dorsal view (fixed specimen); 21, detail of prosternum; 22, detail of foreleg (scales: 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222479/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">
Fig. 
<number box="[1219,1248,1726,1750]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
), due to alcohol fixation period making them paler.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,789,2038]" box="[199,561,1797,1822]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,436,1797,1822]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Female and nymph.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
